Exploring the wonderful region of Ardèche @ardechetourisme and @valleedelagastronomie ⛰️💧🇫🇷

The Ardèche gorges ~ famous for its mountainous landscape, enchanting world of mysterious caves, medieval castles, spectacular waterfalls and beautiful river (perfect for canoeists and kayakers), plus cute little villages and lovely vineyards. Highlights from our time there included…

✓ A private tour of @grottechauvet2 - where we learned all about the first cave art - made over 36,000 years ago 

✓ Lunch with the locals at Auberge la Farigoule - a charming bistrot overlooking vineyards and lavender fields, serving hearty dishes and fantastic desserts.

✓ The most incredible Speleoenology experience @grottesaintmarcel - where we ventured deep into the natural caves and did a blind wine tasting of local wines - including wines aged inside the cave. We also came across some beautiful natural cave pools, which were illuminated by a magical light show.

✓ Super fun wine tasting experience at @domaine_les_amoureuses - where they make some incredible wines aged in amphora. We also loved the local olive oils, chestnut purees and honey. 

✓ A beautiful alfresco dinner, wine and cheese tasting experience, plus an overnight stay @domainedecousignac run by the inspirational organic winemaker Raphael Pommier, where wines are aged with music. Working with local artists and musicians, there is even a different piece of music for each wine blend, composed every year.

Exploring the beautiful region of Drôme in #Provence with @ladrometourisme and @valleedelagastronomie 🌞🇫🇷🍇🪻💜

Drôme is a region filled with picturesque lavender fields, gorgeous vineyards, historical hilltop villages, charming hotels and Michelin starred restaurants. Highlights from our visit included…

✓ A visit to La Garde Adhémar, a medieval hilltop village rated one of the most beautiful villages in France. Whilst there, make sure you visit the church of Saint Michel. Built in the 12th century, it’s one of the gems of the Provençal romanesque style. 

✓ You can also visit ‘Jardin des Herbes’ (the garden of herbs) - inaugurated in 1990, the garden exhibits over 200 varieties of medicinal plants including sage, lavender and geranium plants.

✓ A beautiful alfresco dinner, wine and cheese tasting experience at Bistro 270, a Bib Gourmand restaurant listed in the Michelin guide @domaine_colombier

✓ An overnight stay hotel Domaine du Colombier @domaine_colombier - a 14th-century country house set in stunning gardens with an outdoor pool.

✓ We spent the afternoon by the heated outdoor pool, visiting the vegetable garden, and enjoyed a wine tasting at their winery estate.

The situation : this client came with complaints that her lashes were sore, and she had poor retention. 

The truth : her lashes were glued together, she was not educated on natural lash health and the maintenance or cleansing routine required of extensions. 

The goal : healthy full lashes, 4 week retention, and education on proper home maintenance. 

• first • I deep cleansed with occusoft platnium to exfoliate the presumed ‘years’ of dirt oil makeup etc. then set to removing any poorly placed extensions. 

• second • we did a full set of wispy light extensions for fullness while keeping her natural lash health a top priority. We lashed EVERY SINGLE LASH. Giving her a nice full and guaranteed long lasting retention. 

• third • we sent this client home with a complimentary bottle of lash cleanser, a cleansing brush, a detailed maintenance plan, and access to our 24/7 customer service line for any issues or questions. 

💠 In 9 years I’ve always believed I could lash over anything, in walks this client. I believe clients like this continue to teach •ME• how to do better. How to educate more, and how to reverse damage that was done previously. 

💠 I used to not work over another artists work, but what did that do? Impede me from gaining more confidence in my craft, decrease my knowledge for troubleshooting, and hinder me from fostering new friendships.

When do you need a fill?

During your lash fill we are not only replacing any lost extensions, but we are extending any new growth.

Removing grown out extensions and applying new ones back to the base of the natural lash.

We require you to have 50% of your extensions retained for our fills.

Presenting “A Summer of Risk and Romance”
part 1 - “THE FIRST OFFICER”

My latest series of fine art images explore the ever tempting summer fling. The risks are high and the rules were made clear. But lines were drawn to be crossed and this is a season when reality bends to the will of romance and all logic and sensibility disappears. The inspiration for this collection of images initially came from some very entertaining observations I made along the Italian and French rivieras of playful encounters between sharp men in uniform and delightful well heeled female tourists. The handsome Carabinieri, the athletic first officer of the megayacht, the young tanned bellhop and of course the chiseled Napolitan waiter in Capri, these wonderful men are powerless under the spell of an attractive lady dripping in diamonds, drowned in Number 5 and ready for an off side summer romance. The wedding ring is buried in the safe of the Ritz, the husband is still in New York and her hands are free to bring temptation and a whirlwind of drama and lust to her prey. With jobs on the line and concerned lovers asking their whereabouts there is no turning back. Sometimes lust takes the helm and we are powerless to our own course!

Would you take the chance!? Enjoy the summer!

Proud to present part 1 of my Alpine capsule collection which I designed with @kiton .
Titled „Night and Day“ these exclusive garments were handmade in Naples by @kiton’s master tailors using the very finest of cashmere fabrics. My inspiration for this collection was a throwback to the glory days of alpine sports when men wore blazers and ties proudly as they navigated steep glaciers and traversed crevases on some of the most hostile and challenging terrain. Images of handsome bronzed European men in the 1970’s and 1980’s blazing down the slopes of St Moritz dressed like they were on the way to a formal dinner has always inspired me. Those who know me well are aware of my love for luxury fabrics and my penchant for the finest of tailoring. This next step in my career has been a wonderful experience and to have had the opportunity to design with the masters of Italian style @kiton has been a dream come true. Travelling to Naples last summer to select the fabrics and work on designs with the Paone family was an experience I will never forget. To see the teams of artisans hand stitching each garment step by step is simply breathtaking. Bravo @kiton . My mission is to bring timeless elegance back to the slopes and we are only starting. Thanks to you @mariagiovannapaone , @antoksasha , @twins_piu_one and @daniele.q

Do you feel that your expectations of “life at work” have changed over the years? Let’s discuss…

We are living through a profound rupture in how we relate to work and the people with whom we work. 

People are burned out. 
Laid off. 
Asked to return to offices that don’t feel safe or inspiring. 
Others are craving reconnection but feel out of practice, unsure how to relate face-to-face again. 

I’ve heard from managers who feel as if they are expected to be therapists. And I’ve heard from employees who feel as if they are expected to self-actualize while hitting KPIs.

In short: it’s confusing. It’s tender. And it’s very, very human.

How are you experiencing work right now?

Today I invite you to get curious:

What role does the “negative” person on your team actually play? The one who’s cautious, who tends to catastrophize—what might they be offering the group dynamic?

What in their life might be affecting them before or after work? So long as their approach isn’t personal or targeted, can we reframe their presence as protective rather than problematic?

Not every personality is easy. But that doesn’t mean it’s not valuable.

#TeamDynamics #RelationalIntelligence

We walk into every job carrying the imprint of all the relationships that came before.
The manager who micromanaged us.
The colleague who betrayed our trust.
The parent who never listened.
The sibling who always interrupted.

These dynamics don’t disappear when we sit down at a desk or join a Zoom meeting.

They shape how we give feedback, how we handle conflict, how we speak up—or stay silent.

That’s the relationship legacy. It’s invisible on a resume, but it shapes so much of how we work together.

What do you carry into work with you?

#EstherPerelatWORK

Are you ready for the Arla Great North Swim in June?
@zone3official takes you through ‘sighting’ in open water, so you swim in the right direction and don’t zig zag your way around.

Practicing sighting before the event will make sure you swim in a straight line and ensures you don’t swim further than you need to on the day.
 
If you’re swimming in the pool, why not grab a bottle and use it as a marker at the end of your lane. Try to lift your eyes or head to look at it every few strokes.

If you can practice in the open water, a landmark in the distance is a good marker to swim towards too!

#openwaterswimming #zone3 #zone3official #greatnorthswim2025

As a pro, I’ve learned that success in the pool isn’t just about grinding harder, it’s about training smarter. Here are 3 hacks that have improved my performance over the yearsl:

1. Intensity Control … Not every session should feel like a race. I structure my weeks with purpose, some days are high intensity, others are all about active recovery. 

Learning to manage effort has helped me peak at the right time, not burn out.

2. Consistency Over Everything… Progress doesn’t come from a few epic sessions. It’s the daily grind… the early mornings, the cold water, the drills on repeat. Show up, even when it’s tough. That’s where the real edge is built.

3. Technique First… Speed starts with form. I’m constantly refining my stroke, sometimes with video analysis, sometimes with a coach’s eye. Chasing efficiency in the water has been a bigger game-changer than any strength set.

Train smart. Race hard. Recover harder.

Soon Mabel will be adopted and my heart will be both broken and full. She somehow found my little evergreen bush by my living room window and her mom hid her in there for two months. I fed Mabel and her mom three times per day. They both thanked me before and after every meal. 

I saw that Mabel had a kindness to her and knew she could possibly be someone’s indoor kitty one day, so a few weeks ago, I decided to set a trap and she calmly walked right in. 

I had no idea how special she was until I spent the last few weeks with her. I will miss her dearly but I know she will be going to a great new home. 

There is a waiting list for her because she is absolutely the dreamiest cat anyone could ever be lucky to share a life with. This will be a contest for who can offer her the best, most loving, safest home. 

If you want a loving, super affectionate lap cat who will also play like crazy and make you laugh; a cat so smart and smushy you will be the envy of all of your friends; a cat who will talk to you when you need a friend, Mabel is your baby. 

Mabel is approximately 5 months old now. She has already been spayed and she will be fully vaccinated and ready for her new family before Christmas.

Mabel would prefer to live by herself or with a male dog or cat. 

She is still very scared of everyday normal things and will need time to decompress. 

She also will 100% run outside and needs to be confined to a room or section of the home for at least a few more weeks. 

She will need to be watched as she is a good hider and a fast runner. She needs to feel safe and wants you to sit with her when she eats. 

She also thanks you for feeding her by kissing you, giving you head butts, and lots of rubs and purrs before she takes a bite. 

She answers to the name, “Mama.” 

Adoption form here: https://www.northportcatrescue.org/

From yoga to sunlight, from stillness to service, India’s always had these answers.

Here’s how you can start bringing them into your day:

 🧘🏽 Build inner peace. Through prayer, pranayama, or Surya Namaskar, whatever helps you go inward.
 🌀 Reframe stress. It’s not always a threat; it’s often a challenge, inviting growth.
 📚 Keep learning. Stay open, stay humble, wisdom often comes from unexpected places.
 🤝 Connect and give. Whether through volunteering or simple kindness, acts of service are powerful medicine.
 🎧 Guard your mind. Just like food, what you feed your mind matters; choose content that aligns with your values.
 🙏🏽 Gratitude always. Especially on tough days. It shifts perspective, softens the heart, and brings clarity.

This isn’t about a perfect routine. It’s about returning to what’s always worked.
 Small, consistent steps that help you evolve, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually.
Heal in India. Made in India. Rooted in India.

Calcium supplements…Calcium chewable tablets…Dairy 💊

You want and need K2 to put the calcium into@your bones , you don’t want it in your joints and arteries causing problems 

While these might seem like the best approaches to getting strong bones, consuming them is a wasted effort (rather harmful) if you are deficient in:
Vitamin D3 ☀️ (which every 1 in 2 people are!)
Vitamin K2
Magnesium ⚡

Bone is not all calcium
Each of the above minerals and vitamins are just as important to form the Bone Matrix. They work together as a team synergistically, along with calcium to keep your bones strong and healthy from childhood through the older years.

If we consume too much calcium without sufficient magnesium, Vitamin D3 & K2, the excess calcium is not utilized correctly and may actually become toxic, causing calcification of arteries, bone spurs and heart complications! ❤️‍🩹

So, more calcium & dairy doesn’t mean stronger, healthier bones. You need a healthy bone matrix for strong, young bones, which further determines your bone density and strength.

If you are on treatments like radiation, chemotherapy or taking medications, birth control pills, hormonal treatments, estrogen blockers then these too deteriorate bone density. Thus as a part of your strategy to manage side-effects, it’s important to supplement or at least focus on food sources that make up your bone matrix. 🍽️

	•	A point I missed - importance of sleep for bone health… deep restful sleep 💤 is when bones get stronger and processes like bone remodelling and repair occurs.

Even if you have had a knee/hip replacement you still have to take care of your bones.

A quality life as you age doesn’t mean a good bank balance, access to insurance, doctors and other facilities, but also strong and healthy bones.

Build healthy bones because we will always need them.

Disclaimer: For many medical conditions, you might be required to take calcium supplements. Speak to your doctor about supplements that do not just have calcium but the complete formulation that help build bone matrix.

You feel tired all the time.
Your energy dips for no reason.
You’ve checked your bloodwork.
Your hemoglobin is normal.
Your doctor says things look fine.

But your hair is falling.
Your nails are brittle.
Your skin looks dull.
You’re foggy. You’re restless. 

You’re not imagining it.
There’s something deeper going on.

Have you looked at your ferritin levels?
Because we’ve seen this with so many clients, the problem isn’t always in the obvious markers.
It’s in the reserves.

Ferritin is your iron bank.
Hemoglobin can look perfect while ferritin is quietly running on empty.
This is what we call iron deficiency without anemia (IDWA), which is an early red flag.

This is why a holistic approach matters.
Because health isn’t just about fixing the obvious.
It’s about understanding the systems underneath the symptoms.

Medicine is powerful, and always take what your doctor prescribes.
But pair it with a lifestyle plan:
→ Check your nutrition
→ Understand absorption
→ Address gut health
→ Work on rest and recovery
→ And always recheck.

Sometimes the answer is that simple.
And sometimes it takes zooming out, not digging deeper.

That’s the beauty of integrative and lifestyle medicine — it doesn’t replace, it complements.

I met @winnieharlow seven years ago on a Dior job I felt completely out of place at: she was already a star, along all her other super cool supermodel friends, and I never felt smaller than at that table. 
Trying to ‘earn‘ my place, I was showing my portfolio, to prove I somehow belonged among them, that I too had done great things in the industry. 
I’ll never forget how she said ‘ girl stop that, we know you must be good, you wouldn’t be here otherwise ‘ and I loved her from that moment. 
That comment, somehow both harsh and uplifting, forced me to believe in myself more than I actually did at the time.
This is really coming full circle, as we meet again on the set of our @VOGUEarabia cover, and she is brighter than ever, still the realest and sweetest in the room, an absolute delight to work with as she NEVER fails a single shot. 🥂🍾✨ HAPPY NEW YEAR! 💫 ⭐️🎆
I became a lot more private in 2024 and I don’t share as much as I used to of my personal life and what’s in my head, but what I used to say 10 years ago still stands today: I wouldn’t do what I do if I couldn’t share it with you. 🥰
As most people on social media, I tend to compare myself to others, feeling like I am never enough, there is always someone with bigger campaigns, bigger covers, bigger following: 
But when I meet you in real life, in different countries, people of all ages and cultures, hearing your stories and how I am sometimes a part of it, inspiring you to go after your dreams, I feel more than ENOUGH.
Thank you for allowing me to share my journey with you, for all your support and for always making me want to strive further ✨
Cheers to you and to all the people in my life that I ADORE but I didn’t write to cause I am allergic to NYE texts lol 🥂
💞 home for the next week 🏝️🧳🐠☀️

These are my favorite encounters, 
true beauty in all kinds of age, shape, ethnicity.

AND ANOTHER ONE! @voguearabia 📸🖤

This June, #VogueArabia’s annual Saudi issue salutes the majestic Arabian leopard, a symbol of national pride, and one of the most noble animals in the Kingdom’s tauna. Listed as critically endangered with fewer than 200 of its kind remaining in the wild, the iconic cat is the subject of intense conservation efforts spearheaded by organizations including the Royal Commission for AlUla, the Arabian Leopard Fund, and Catmosphere, founded by HRH Princess Reema Bint Bandar Al Saud (@rosalsaud). From this year on, the animal will also be honored every February 10 by the United Nations General Assembly on the International Day of the Arabian Leopard. In celebration of its new era, the royal pens an exclusive open letter for this month’s cover story. “The Arabian leopard has become revered in Arabian folklore and tradition, embodying the essence of grace, power, and resilience. Its depiction in art, literature, fashion, and poetry reflects a deep-seated appreciation for its graceful form and elusive nature,” she writes.
In a month when fashion goes wild, @yaralnamlah shares our cover with the spotted feline. Head to the link in bio to read the complete address.

Visited Turin with mom and sis 🤍
She wanted to see Venaria Reale and so I brought her, and while she marveled at the white vaults for the first time I reminisced how I had the entire location closed off for a day for one of my shootings.
Then we went to the Egyptian museum, and as she marveled at the ancient statues I reminisced how I was the first fashion photographer to ever shoot in the most important temples of Luxor and the tomb of Nefertari, the most exquisitely conserved tomb in ancient history, a place that accepts visits of merely 15 minutes a day. The things I’ve done, the places I’ve seen.
I will never take it for granted. I really lived a life worth of a movie and I owe it to you Mamma, the first to ever believe in me, when you first saw me from across the livingroom at 15 and said ‘ you really catch fire when you have the camera in your hands ‘ 
📸
I love you.

26th floor 🔑

I get a lot of freedom when it comes to creativity, but ultimately a campaign, no matter how high fashion the brand might be, still needs to sell the product.
The beauty of women is my one true love, so I could never imagine myself shooting without focusing on that. I found interesting merging my need with my client’s need in these portraits, where the heel remains the protagonist, but the veiled beauty behind still attracts the eye further deep into the picture.
📷

I dreamt all my life of shooting a Vogue cover, and I just had 5 in a MONTH… my life really is a movie and it exceeded all expectations.
My heart is full of gratitude 🤍 but also PRIDE, as I know just a handful of Italian photographers can say they experienced this kind of success, and NONE of them were women. 
To realize I am the first female Italian photographer in history to hold this many Vogue covers just hits different. 
🥹🙏🏼
